{{legend|#7f7f7f|A poll shows a statistical tie between support of and opposition to same-sex marriage.<br>(Statistical tie: Not distinguishable at 95% confidence. Difference between support and opposition is < 0.842 of the 95% sampling error (< 1.65σ).)}}
{{legend|#E4717A|A poll shows at least a plurality, and possibly a majority, of that state's population opposes same-sex marriage.}}
{{legend|#8B0000|A poll reports a significant finding that a majority of that state's population opposes same-sex marriage.<br>(95% significant: Result is > 0.653 of the 95% sampling error (> 1.28σ) above 50%.}}
